com.nutiteq.packagemanager

Class NutiteqPackageManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.nutiteq.packagemanager.PackageManager
      • com.nutiteq.packagemanager.NutiteqPackageManager

  • public class NutiteqPackageManager
extends PackageManager
    Offline map package manager that uses Nutiteq online service for map package downloads.
    After packages are downloaded, they can be used offline without any connection to the server.

      • NutiteqPackageManager

        public NutiteqPackageManager(java.lang.String source,
                             java.lang.String dataFolder)
        Constructs a NutiteqPackageManager object, given application context and data folder.
        The data folder must exist before creating a new package manager and it is assumed to be persistent.
        Note: the package manager must be explicitly started using start() method!
        Parameters:
        source - Name of the package source. Currently "nutiteq.mbstreets" source is available
        dataFolder - The folder where downloaded packages are kept. It must exist and must be writable.
